  "text": "A number of studies elucidating the fundamental mechanisms of biological systems suggest that noise is an \"essential ingredient\" in these systems, without which they cannot function. For example, noise plays an important role in molecular transitions or interactions that control cellular behavior (e.g., how cells acquire fate) [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, several mathematical models used to describe biological processes require a noise term to adequately model the behaviour of these processes.",
